    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-07-18T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="238" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d238">
                <head>No. 238.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 18,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 634.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to the instruction No. 562, of
                        the 31st of March last, of this Department to you concerning the Venezuela
                        debts, I now inclose<note n="*" xml:id="d238fn1">For inclosure see inclosure
                            to document No. 203, under Germany, <hi rend="italic">ante.</hi>
                    </note>
                        herewith for your information a copy of a note from Count Hatzfeldt, the
                        minister of foreign affairs of Germany, in which he states that the imperial
                        German Government will ageer to whatever the other nations interested
                        approve, with due regard to its treaty rights.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FEED’K T. FRELINGHUYSEN.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
